[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND OUTCOME CORRELATION ───────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated bot responses                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Action-execution records                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active tool-surface version                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Care-coordination-specific retention]                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - HIPAA's six-year minimum                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - State-specific retention rules where applicable      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Cross-entity data-sharing record retention per       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      data-use agreements                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation]                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - 30-day readmission rate                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - 30-day ED-revisit rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Time-to-post-discharge follow-up                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Referral-completion rate                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Appointment-attendance rate                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Medication-reconciliation-completion rate            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Care-coordinator-workload offload                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient-reported coordination experience (CAHPS or   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      similar)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort outcome disparity monitoring              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Action-completion rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Warm-handoff completion rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool-call latency and error rates                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of escalations    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (care-coordinators) tag failure modes      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool-surface revisions and prompt revisions driven   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      by review findings                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    tool-and-prompt-revision proposals]                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care-coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-system orchestration as architectural primitive.** The bot's value is fundamentally in integrating across systems. The tool surface is the architectural floor; the integration depth determines the bot's usefulness.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-coordinator-workforce integration as primary safety architecture.** The bot is deployed with backstop care-coordinator capacity. The handoff is warm. Capacity is sized to the patient population.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Family-caregiver-consent posture as explicit architectural element.** The bot's interactions with family caregivers are scoped, audited, and revocable.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Transitions-of-care discipline as architectural focus.** Care transitions are the highest-risk windows; the bot's discipline around transitions is structurally enforced.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Social-determinants signal escalation as architectural pattern.** Sustained patterns of missed coordination tasks route to care-management or to social-care navigation per institutional configuration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-entity data-sharing posture with appropriate governance.** Where the bot operates across legal entities, data-sharing arrangements are explicit and enforced.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Action-confirmation discipline.** High-impact actions (scheduling, rescheduling, message-sending on the patient's behalf) require explicit confirmation; low-impact actions (lookups) do not.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every cross-system fact is grounded in a tool call. No fabricated referral status, no fabricated appointment times, no fabricated benefit details.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **End-of-life and bereavement awareness.** The bot's behavior shifts gracefully for patients on palliative or hospice care and for bereaved family caregivers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement, action-completion, warm-handoff completion, outcome metrics vary by language, channel, condition mix, age cohort, sex, social-determinants posture, and family-caregiver presence. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed regularly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the EHR/FHIR, the scheduling system, the referral system, the benefits-eligibility system, the care-management workflow, the transportation provider, or the social-care navigation system is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully with clear messaging about the limitation and explicit fallback to phone-based support.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
